<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-28T18:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-28T18:34:00-05:00" n="714" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d714">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2589: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract—Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-29T08:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">June 29,
                                        1922—8 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 30—3:54
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Department’s telegram of June 22, 4 p.m. …</p>
                        <p>Considering that the only necessary expense will be that of maintaining
                            the existing organization, I recommend that action be deferred for a
                            short time as developments which may change the railway situation are
                            liable to take place.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>